Very well put, Greg. Inspect the parts, replace only those showing wear or 
stress or fail basic tests. This is the difference between "tune-ups" and 
maintenance inspections.

At 06:07 AM 10/24/2002, you wrote:

>Hi Alan,
>  After a "Tune-Up" it would be virtually impossible to determine which 
> component was at fault: points, cap, rotor, wires, vacuum, valves, dwell 
> & timing gives you only a 1 in 8 chance of guessing it right. The magic 
> is in the procedure, not the parts.
